<br>
Also, when I went to SolA to buy my Tink Bag and had 5400ish pp on me, I was 100+ stones over the limit, but my AC was still 700+. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ussyxz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ssyxz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 416<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 10:27:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11612.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weight penalties</span><hr size=1> I started working on the weight penalties a long time ago, and discovered that it only applies to the first 15 stones/pounds/units/whatever you go overweight.<br>
<br>
Unfortunatly, I became bored with them, and quit working on it.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><b>Ssyxz<br>59 Iksar Master<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=178226">Magelo</a></b</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 10:49:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11612.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weight penalties</span><hr size=1> I got a graphing calcultor that can find the line of best fit for nonlinear equations.<br>
